Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says interventions have been taken by government to stimulate economic growth. CAPE TOWN - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says interventions have been taken by government to stimulate economic growth.Ramaphosa has highlighted government's Nine Point and Industrial Policy Action Plans as two initiatives to promote job creation and expand the country's economy.The deputy president was questioned on interventions taken to profile South Africa as a lucrative investment destination. We re on track to revamping business and economic processes in our country. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)